[[File:Juozas Ambrazevičius-Brazaitis.jpg|thumb|right|Juozas Ambrazevičius in 1925]]
'''Juozas Ambrazevičius''' or '''Juozas Brazaitis''' (December 9, 1903 in [[Trakiškiai (Marijampolė)|Trakiškiai]],<!-- not to be confused with Trakiškiai (Varėna) or Trakiškės --> [[Marijampolė parish]]<!-- Marijampolės valsčius --> – October 28, 1974 in [[South Orange, New Jersey]]), was a [[Lithuania]]n literary historian, better known for his political career and [[nationalist]]ic views. He was the acting [[Prime Minister of Lithuania|Prime Minister]] of the [[Provisional Government of Lithuania]] from June 23, 1941 to August 5, 1941.

==Academic career==

Ambrazevičius studied literature at [[University of Lithuania]] in Kaunas and [[University of Bonn]]. From 1927 he lectured on [[Lithuanian literature]] and folklore in [[Kaunas]]. By the end of the 1930s he got involved in numerous organizations for literature teachers and scientists. His major works include ''Theory of Literature'' (''Literatūros teorija'' in 1930), two-volume ''A History of World Literature'' (''Visoutinė literatūros istorija'' in 1931-1932), ''[[Juozas Tumas-Vaižgantas|Vaižgantas]]'' (in 1936), three-volume ''New Readings'' (''Naujieji skaitymai''), ''Lithuanian Writers'' (''Lietuvių rašytojai'' in 1938). He also worked on the editorial staff of national daily ''Lietuva'' (''Lithuania'') and Catholic daily ''XX amžius'' (''The 20th Century''). He would sometimes use [[pseudonym]] Servus to write for these newspapers. During [[World War II]] he edited an underground periodical ''Į laisvę'' (''Towards Freedom'') which he later revived in Germany and in the United States.

==Grave==
In 2012, Ambrazevičius remains were transported from the United States to Lithuania and were reburied in the [[churchyard]] of [[Christ's Resurrection Church, Kaunas|Christ's Resurrection Church]] in [[Kaunas]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kaune perlaidojami 1941-ųjų Laikinosios vyriausybės vadovo Juozo Brazaičio palaikai |url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/lietuva/kaune-perlaidojami-1941-uju-laikinosios-vyriausybes-vadovo-juozo-brazaicio-palaikai-56-219988 |website=15min.lt |accessdate=20 May 2012}}</ref>

